summary: SummaryHighlightsSustainable PackagingHigh Impact Mascara is Clinique's bestselling mascara. Kicks up the volume and length of each and every lash.
details: DetailsBenefitsHigh Impact Mascara is your go-to for buildable volume and natural lashes dialed up a notch.Rich black pigments give lashes intense color, adding to the drama.Create the look you want with this lengthening and volumizing mascara, from your-lashes-but-better to lush, bold drama.The soft fiber brush was designed to comb and define every lash.The Clinique Eye Safety Promise:Safe for sensitive eyesThis mascara is also:Dermatologist testedAllergy testedFragrance freeFormulated WithoutParabensPhthalatesOilFragranceItem 2153781How To UseStart at lash roots, wiggling mascara brush up to lash tips. Repeat to build. For lower lashes, hold wand vertically. Avoid pumping the brush in the container - this adds air that can dry out mascara. To prevent clumping, let mascara dry between coats.Remove with Take The Day Off Makeup Remover For Lids, Lashes & Lips.IngredientsWater / Aqua / Eau, Copernicia Cerifera (Carnauba) Wax / Cera Carnauba / Cire De Carnauba, Stearic Acid, Glyceryl Stearate, Polyisobutene, Silica, Acrylates Copolymer, Aminomethyl Propanediol, VP / Eicosene Copolymer, Sodium Hyaluronate, Lauroyl Lysine, Pantethine, Melanin, Panthenol, Hydrolyzed Wheat Protein, Ethylhexylglycerin, Hydroxyethylcellulose, Calcium Aluminum Borosilicate, PVP, Acacia Senegal Gum, Isostearic Acid, Simethicone, Dimethicone PEG-8 Polyacrylate, Urea, Glycerin, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Sodium Lauryl Sulfate, PEG-8 Dimethicone, Disodium EDTA, Chlorphenesin, Sodium Dehydroacetate, Phenoxyethanol. May Contain: Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499), Yellow 5 Lake (CI 19140), Chromium Oxide Greens (CI 77288), Mica, Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Ferric Ferrocyanide (CI 77510), Chromium Hydroxide Green (CI 77289), Carmine (CI 75470), Bismuth Oxychloride (CI 77163), Aluminum Powder (CI 77000), Bronze Powder (CI 77400), Blue 1 Lake (CI 42090), Ultramarines (CI 77007).Please be aware that ingredient lists may change or vary from time to time. Please refer to the ingredient list on the product package you receive for the most up to date list of ingredients.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Start at lash roots, wiggling mascara brush up to lash tips. Repeat to build. For lower lashes, hold wand vertically. Avoid pumping the brush in the container - this adds air that can dry out mascara. To prevent clumping, let mascara dry between coats.Remove with Take The Day Off Makeup Remover For Lids, Lashes & Lips.

reviews.headline: Been using this mascara for years!
reviews.comments: I have tried other mascaras over the years, and Clinique High Impact Volumizing mascara is by far the best!  It wears nicely without smudging, it is easy to get off, and it makes my lashes look so much fuller!

reviews.headline: Great mascara in a great color
reviews.comments: This black honey color is just beautiful

reviews.headline: I Love This Mascara!
reviews.comments: I got the mini version of this mascara awhile back and just used it for the first time today. I was skeptical because the brush looked kind of generic, but once I put it on I was so impressed! This is probably my new favorite mascara. No clumping, separates my eyelashes well, no flaking at the end of the day. 10/10

reviews.headline: stings
reviews.comments: I'm so bummed i love the color and the way it applies. This mascara is not waterproof, when my eyes water this product runs into my eyes and stings

reviews.headline: So flakey
reviews.comments: I regret giving this a try. While it looked nice, it was fairly clumpy and a nightmare to take off. Flaked all over my face.

reviews.headline: Yes
reviews.comments: Great coverage makes lashes look long without clumping

reviews.headline: A disappointment
reviews.comments: It's just a brown mascara. There's nothing remotely black honey about this. It's also EXTREMELY natural on the lashes. The photo is after two very laborious coats. Just an utter disappointment of a cash grab if you ask me. I highly regret purchasing.

reviews.headline: I love this mascara!
reviews.comments: This mascara goes on without clumping and it leaves my eyelashes looking very natural.  I would highly recommend it!

reviews.headline: Fairly clumpy
reviews.comments: I like the shade, it's dark but it comes on goopy & looks cheap

reviews.headline: No
reviews.comments: It's not the worst but definitely not the best. I find I have to really lay it on and do several layers for it to look good.

reviews.headline: Clinique Black Honey mascara
reviews.comments: As I don't like black mascara on me I used brown for several years until I found this product. The Black Honey colour adds a softer colour to my lashes and is a touch more interesting with my brown eyes I tend to stock up on a few when I am on my holidays.

reviews.headline: Clinique black honey mascara
reviews.comments: I love this product. The color is beautiful. I like the brush  in this mascara. It goes in well and last. I like that it's not waterproof. Creates bolder lashes.

reviews.headline: I love this
reviews.comments: I absolutely love this mascara it's hard for me to find one that doesn't flake or burn my eyes and this one is perfect and doesn't do any of that and the color makes the green in my eyes pop.

reviews.headline: Best
reviews.comments: Thus is my go to. I'll give a drugstore brand a try and after one wearing it's in the garbage can

reviews.headline: It's alright
reviews.comments: This mascara is ok for the price but i find it to be very lack luster. I have very curled up semi voluminous natural lashes and after curling my lashes more there still wasnt much that the mascara did. It didnt add any more volume or length personally so i think if you have straight or downward pointed lashes this may not work well for you at all. The color also just didnt show up for me. It just looked dark I couldn't tell there was even a tint of color. It may be better with a white base but i thought for 26 dollars it might have a better color payoff. Thats on me I guess. The prose though are that it doesnt clump your lashes together and it gives your lashes a very natural look if thats what you want. And once it's dry it doesn't go anywhere for at least a few hours. Id likely check after a couple hours just to make sure. I did have some slight smudging on the bottom but it was pretty minimal after so many hours of wear. Regardless ill stick with my nars climax mascara personally < 3

reviews.headline: Extremely happy
reviews.comments: I've been using this mascara for almost half a year, and I couldn't be happier with it. The texture is great - it goes on evenly and never clumps. I love how it makes my eyes pop, and the color is absolutely amazing.

reviews.headline: A great everyday mascara
reviews.comments: This mascara has always intrigued me and I finally gave it a try. My go to is the high impact zero gravity mascara, but this seems like a cult favorite. It gives my lashes length without getting clumpy. My only negative would be that it's marketed as a tubing mascara but it doesn't behave like one. It doesn't wash off in tubes, it just smears off like any other mascara. The zero gravity version is very very clearly a tubing mascara, while this is not. I'm still happy with it though!

reviews.headline: So disappointing):
reviews.comments: It's a nice color but the formula is absolutely horrible, my lashes curl easily and it brought them down horribly

reviews.headline: No no no
reviews.comments: This mascara is the worst. Clumps and runs down your face. Want my $$ back

reviews.headline: Product separates from lashes.
reviews.comments: I thought this was going to be a winner (great branding) but every time I wore it (only 4x) it smudged and collected on my eyelids. I'm going to get a store credit from Ulta, and buy YSL's brown instead.

faceoff_positive.comments: I love this mascara. It does wonders to every eye lash type (unless you use to much, of course). When using the brush correctly it volumizes, lenthens as it spreads your lashes out. If you put on a lot at once when its not dry it will clump and look bad. So,be careful with the amount you use! Wonderful product!
faceoff_positive.headline: Best mascara!

faceoff_negative.comments: This is a nice mascara that does give volume. I've found that it does clump especially on my lower lashes. Half the time I'm removing the extra with a Q-tip, or trying to separate the lashes with a small eyelash brush. Even after taking off all my makeup the night before, the next morning I awake with smudges under my eyes from the mascara I didn't notice was still there. Will try another Clinque mascara to see if I find my all time favorite.
faceoff_negative.headline: Nice, but clumps!
